01:32:53,930 --> 01:32:56,020
我们申请不到搜索票
We couldn't get a warrant.

1423
01:32:56,200 --> 01:32:57,600
(1972年9月7日  加州  瓦列霍)

1424
01:32:57,770 --> 01:33:00,830
去年我们安排李和社工见面
Last year we arranged for Leigh to get help from a social worker.

1425
01:33:01,000 --> 01:33:05,700
他只去了两次
He only went twice. We saw him recently for the first time in nine months.

1426
01:33:05,880 --> 01:33:08,840
最近我婆婆带他来看小孩  这是九个月来第一次见面
My mother-in-law brought him by to see the new baby.

1427
01:33:09,010 --> 01:33:12,000
后来我就去找社工了解状况
After he left, I went to see that social worker.

1428
01:33:12,180 --> 01:33:15,150
他不能透露病人病情  我就直接问他
He couldn't talk about a former patient, so I just asked him straight out

1429
01:33:15,320 --> 01:33:17,950
李会不会杀人
if he thought Leigh was capable of killing people.

1430
01:33:18,120 --> 01:33:21,450
-由于病人保密法则...  -社工说他会杀人
-Because of patient confidentiality... -The man said yes.

1431
01:33:23,190 --> 01:33:25,365
你们为什么九个月没见过他? 
Why hadn't you seen him in nine months? 

1432
01:33:25,366 --> 01:33:27,250
 他在圣塔罗莎的学校上课
He's going to school in Santa Rosa.

1433
01:33:27,430 --> 01:33:30,870
-圣塔罗莎?他住在哪里?  -他的拖车屋
-Santa Rosa? Where is he living? -In his trailer.

1434
01:33:31,030 --> 01:33:32,760
-在圣塔罗莎?  -索诺犸郡
-In Santa Rosa? -Sonoma County.

1435
01:33:32,940 --> 01:33:35,130
我们不用透过瓦列霍检察官
We wouldn't have to go through the Vallejo DA.

1436
01:33:35,310 --> 01:33:38,330
你们有11个月没问过他话  现在要去搜他的拖车屋?
It's been 11 months since you talked to this guy, and now you wanna search his trailer?

1437
01:33:38,510 --> 01:33:40,170
能找到证物最好
If we find something, great.

1438
01:33:40,340 --> 01:33:43,510
不然也能采到指纹和双手的笔迹
If not, we get his prints and handwriting samples from both hands.

1439
01:33:43,680 --> 01:33:45,710
我以为莫瑞尔推翻了你的论点
I thought Sherwood shut you down.

1440
01:33:46,880 --> 01:33:49,040
我想请别人鉴定
What if I can get a second opinion?

1441
01:33:50,450 --> 01:33:52,890
我不想反驳莫瑞尔的鉴定  我是他一手栽培的
I don't wanna step on Sherwood's toes. He trained me at this.

1442
01:33:53,060 --> 01:33:55,790
我只想知道嫌犯能不能双手并用
Terry, all I need to know is if the suspect is ambidextrous.

1443
01:33:55,960 --> 01:33:59,790
他是不是可能用另一只手写信
Could he possibly have written those letters with his other hand?

1444
01:34:01,100 --> 01:34:02,220
我只告诉你
Between you and me?

1445
01:34:02,400 --> 01:34:05,800
笔迹鉴定有不同的学派
Because there are differing schools of thought on this.

1446
01:34:07,500 --> 01:34:11,340
只要拿到他另一只手的笔迹  如果他是黄道带就会符合
Get the samples of his other hand. If he's the Zodiac, you'll get a match.

1447
01:34:11,510 --> 01:34:14,310
这是泰瑞目前的想法
That's the current thinking, according to Terry Pascoe.

1448
01:34:14,480 --> 01:34:17,240
我也问了愿意作证的心理医师
Meanwhile, I spoke to a psychologist who'd be willing to testify

1449
01:34:17,410 --> 01:34:20,580
他说像黄道带这种性格多变的人
that someone who undergoes a personality change like Zodiac

1450
01:34:20,750 --> 01:34:23,580
生理上也会改变  比如改变笔迹
would manifest it physically, altering his handwriting.

1451
01:34:23,750 --> 01:34:27,350
所以莫瑞尔的笔迹鉴定会不符合
Which is why Sherwood couldn't get a match from Allen's samples.

1452
01:34:27,520 --> 01:34:29,690
泰瑞  心理医师和钱尼夫妇
We got Terry Pascoe, this psychology guy,

1453
01:34:29,860 --> 01:34:32,560
有他们就能申请搜索票
coupled with Cheney It could be enough for a warrant.

1454
01:34:32,730 --> 01:34:34,060
请钱尼做正式笔录
Get Cheney on the record.

1455
01:34:34,280 --> 01:34:38,190
他就会自称为黄道带
And that he would call himself Zodiac.

1456
01:34:38,350 --> 01:34:40,750
-是的  -你愿意在
-Yes. -And you're willing to swear to this,

1457
01:34:40,920 --> 01:34:42,860
高等法庭发誓作证?
under oath, in Superior Court?

1458
01:34:43,030 --> 01:34:44,360
毫不会犹豫
Without any hesitation.

1459
01:34:44,530 --> 01:34:47,760
非常感谢你  钱尼先生
Thank you very much, Mr. Cheney. Thank you very much for your time.

1460
01:34:47,930 --> 01:34:48,550
谢谢你
Thank you.

1461
01:34:48,650 --> 01:34:50,040
嫌犯名叫亚瑟・李・艾伦
Suspect is Arthur Leigh Allen.

1462
01:34:50,040 --> 01:34:53,870
家住加州圣塔罗莎日落拖车公园
Lives in Sunset Trailer Court in Santa Rosa, California.

1463
01:34:53,870 --> 01:34:55,540
体貌特征:
Physical description.

1464
01:34:55,540 --> 01:34:57,870
艾伦高大  体型粗壮  
Allen is similar in height, weight and build

1465
01:34:57,870 --> 01:35:01,080
与贝湖行刺案所描述的案犯特征一致
to a man seen at Lake Berryessa on the day of the stabbings.

1466
01:35:01,080 --> 01:35:03,960
但是  他和加州的那个案子体貌描述不一样
I understand he doesn't look much like the San Francisco composite.

1467
01:35:03,960 --> 01:35:05,580
是的  高大粗壮只是粗略描述
True. Height and weight are sketchy,

1468
01:35:05,620 --> 01:35:07,910
但是从都是粗壮的白种人这点看是一致的
but lumbering Caucasian with a crew cut is right on.

1469
01:35:07,910 --> 01:35:10,280
我们对从孩子口中得到的口供并没有多少信心
We never had much confidence in the composite from the kids.

1470
01:35:10,280 --> 01:35:12,410
那晚说是见到黄道带的巡警
The patrolman who say Zodiac that night

1471
01:35:12,410 --> 01:35:13,960
说他和草图上的并不相像
said he didn't look much like the sketch.

1472
01:35:14,000 --> 01:35:15,540
军用靴鞋印
Military boot prints.

1473
01:35:15,540 --> 01:35:18,370
艾伦入过海军  穿10号半的鞋
Allen was in the Navy. Wears a size 10-and-a-half.

1474
01:35:18,370 --> 01:35:20,910
与贝湖案的大小一致
Same size as the prints found at Berryessa.

1475
01:35:20,910 --> 01:35:22,700
那枪呢?
What about gun?

1476
01:35:22,700 --> 01:35:27,370
切尼说他有好几种武器  我们会在搜捕令中写明
Cheney says Allen owns several firearms. We'll list them in the warrant.

1477
01:35:27,370 --> 01:35:30,240
-密码呢  -可能是在海军中学到的  
-And the ciphers. -Could be code training in the Navy,

1478
01:35:30,240 --> 01:35:33,080
也有人作证说艾伦过去画过
and people have seen Allen with ciphers in the past.

1479
01:35:33,080 --> 01:35:34,200
真的吗?  谁?
Really? Who?

1480
01:35:34,200 --> 01:35:37,080
他的嫂子及他的哥哥叫做费尔・塔克
That would be his sister-in-law and a man named Phil Tucker

1481
01:35:37,080 --> 01:35:39,490
他哥哥在瓦列霍的公共泳池工作
that he worked with at a public pool in Vallejo.

1482
01:35:39,490 --> 01:35:43,080
费尔・塔克还告诉我们他和弟弟曾
And Phil Tucker told us about a conversation that he had with Allen

1483
01:35:43,080 --> 01:35:45,870
把手电装到枪管上
about how to attach a flashlight to the barrel of a gun.

1484
01:35:45,870 --> 01:35:49,200
从密码和手电上就给了我们2个证据
That gives us two sources on the ciphers and two on the flashlight.

1485
01:35:49,200 --> 01:35:51,330
那他对孩子的恐吓呢?
What about his threats on children?

1486
01:35:51,330 --> 01:35:53,160
嫌犯曾在小学工作
Suspect worked for elementary schools

1487
01:35:53,160 --> 01:35:56,490
因为猥亵于1968年3-4月间被开除
and was fired for molestation in March, April '68.

1488
01:35:56,490 --> 01:35:59,200
-这可能给他以动机  -至少  这是家庭因素
-Could give him motive. -At the very least, it's home turf.

1489
01:35:59,200 --> 01:36:01,370
从他的恐吓信2个主要环节看  
He'd have knowledge of bus routes,

1490
01:36:01,370 --> 01:36:03,910
他对校车路线很熟悉
which the two major threats centered around.

1491
01:36:03,910 --> 01:36:05,660
炸弹呢?
What about the bomb?

1492
01:36:07,080 --> 01:36:09,120
艾伦的工作是化学师
Allen works as a chemist.

1493
01:36:09,120 --> 01:36:10,660
还对地理相当熟悉
Take him through the geography.

1494
01:36:10,660 --> 01:36:12,240
瓦列霍谋杀犯
Vallejo murders.

1495
01:36:12,240 --> 01:36:15,830
艾伦在瓦列霍曾和他妈妈  在她的地下室居住
Allen lives in Vallejo with his mother in her basement.

1496
01:36:15,830 --> 01:36:19,120
贝湖案  2个人被刺的那天
Berryessa murder. On the day that the two kids were stabbed

1497
01:36:19,120 --> 01:36:21,870
他的邻居发现在他的车里有带血的匕首
his neighbor saw bloody knives in his truck

1498
01:36:21,870 --> 01:36:24,870
不过他的解释是用来杀鸡了
which he claimed were used to kill a chicken.

1499
01:36:24,870 --> 01:36:26,830
他辩解了?
Does he have any alibis?

1500
01:36:26,830 --> 01:36:29,580
是的  但是要不是他见过
He claimed he did, but he's been unable to produce the names

1501
01:36:29,580 --> 01:36:32,960
他不可能编造对  贝湖案那对情侣的名字
of the couple he supposedly met on the day of Berryessa.

1502
01:36:32,960 --> 01:36:35,410
底线是艾伦不可能会辩解全部事
The bottom line is that Allen can't alibi up on anything.

1503
01:36:35,410 --> 01:36:37,330
滨河  瓦列霍  湖或者我们
Riverside, Vallejo, the lake or us.

1504
01:36:37,330 --> 01:36:39,620
-你要不要说说名字的事?  -什么名字?
-You want to tell me about the name? -What name?

1505
01:36:39,620 --> 01:36:40,830
黄道带
Zodiac.

1506
01:36:40,830 --> 01:36:44,830
艾伦戴的手表不但有那个单词  还有那个十字图案
Allen wears a watch that bears both the word and crosshair symbol.

1507
01:36:44,830 --> 01:36:46,280
他还向切尼提起过
And he mentioned Zodiac to Cheney

1508
01:36:46,280 --> 01:36:48,870
事情发生一年半之前在任何信件中都可以看到
a year and a half before it appeared in any letter.

1509
01:36:52,040 --> 01:36:54,580
-约翰  -非常好  伙计们
-John... -That's pretty good, guys.

1510
01:36:54,580 --> 01:36:57,580
-我们也是这么想的  -让我们把他绳之以法吧
-We think so, too. -Let's take it to a judge.

1511
01:36:58,600 --> 01:37:05,170
(1972年9月14日  加州  圣塔罗莎  日落拖车公园A-7号)

1512
01:37:17,760 --> 01:37:19,090
艾伦先生?
Mr. Allen?

1513
01:37:19,260 --> 01:37:23,590
圣塔罗莎警局  我们有搜索票
This is the Santa Rosa Police Department. We have a warrant to search your residence.

1514
01:37:34,970 --> 01:37:36,300
有人吗?
Hello?

1515
01:37:44,950 --> 01:37:46,850
我去问附近的邻居
I'll check with the neighbors.

1516
01:37:48,490 --> 01:37:49,980
-关门  -关门
-Close the door. -Close the door,

1517
01:37:50,160 --> 01:37:52,210
有鼠类动物跑来跑去
there's rodents running around.

1518
01:38:04,870 --> 01:38:07,390
邻居说他半小时前闪人了
Neighbor said he tore out of here about a half-hour ago.

1519
01:38:07,570 --> 01:38:11,060
-有人向他告密?  -他回来前我们不会走
-You think somebody tipped him? -We're not leaving till he comes back.

1520
01:38:17,620 --> 01:38:18,950
我去查后面
I'll check the back.

1521
01:38:32,230 --> 01:38:33,960
-老天  -什么?
-Jesus. -What?

1522
01:38:34,130 --> 01:38:35,570
松鼠
Squirrels.

1523
01:38:37,140 --> 01:38:38,630
这家伙超变态的
Piece of work, this guy.

1524
01:38:45,940 --> 01:38:48,140
不只一件  两件蓝色风衣
Not one, but two blue windbreakers.

1525
01:38:48,310 --> 01:38:51,870
-史坦命案现场那件?  -我们会送去验血比对
-Like the Stine scene? -We'll have those checked for blood.

1526
01:38:52,980 --> 01:38:56,720
还有一对黑色手套
And a pair of black gloves.

1527
01:38:57,120 --> 01:39:00,220
男性七号大小  跟计程车上那对一样
Men's seven, just like the ones we found in the cab.

1528
01:39:00,830 --> 01:39:03,260
鞋子和手套的尺寸也符合
Well, he's got the same size shoes and gloves as Z.

1529
01:39:03,430 --> 01:39:05,450
搞不好只是巧合
Probably just a coincidence.

1530
01:39:05,630 --> 01:39:10,260
我找到一把枪  你看  不对  是两把枪
Dave, I got a gun. Check that. Two guns.

1531
01:39:11,070 --> 01:39:13,830
两把点22口径手枪  一把自动手枪  一把左轮手枪
They're both .22s. One automatic, one revolver.

1532
01:39:14,010 --> 01:39:15,340
这倒很有趣
Well, that's interesting.

1533
01:39:15,510 --> 01:39:18,640
他的衣橱也有一把M1步枪
Because he happens to have an M-1 rifle here in the closet.

1534
01:39:18,810 --> 01:39:21,340
向那些可爱的学童下手
For little darlings bouncing off buses.

1535
01:39:22,880 --> 01:39:24,370
有人来了
Someone's here.

1536
01:39:31,520 --> 01:39:34,720
哈  亚瑟  记得我们吗?
Hello, Arthur. Remember us?

1537
01:39:56,480 --> 01:39:58,570
-没有证据  -笔迹呢?
-No. -On the handwriting?

1538
01:39:58,750 --> 01:40:01,810
弹道  指纹跟笔迹都不符合
Ballistics, no match. Prints, no match. Writing, no match.

1539
01:40:01,990 --> 01:40:05,920
双手的笔迹吗?  双手的笔迹我们都有
On both hands, right? Because we got handwriting from both his hands.

1540
01:40:06,090 --> 01:40:07,420
双手笔迹都不符合
And neither hand matches.

1541
01:40:07,590 --> 01:40:11,260
-别管莫瑞尔  问其他专家的意见  -两位  他不是凶手
-Forget Sherwood. Let's get another opinion. -Fellas, he's not your guy.

1542
01:40:17,870 --> 01:40:19,360
可恶
Damn it.

1543
01:40:28,380 --> 01:40:29,940
你想怎样?
What do you want?

1544
01:40:30,110 --> 01:40:31,670
休息一阵子?
Time off?

1545
01:40:33,020 --> 01:40:34,580
抱一下?
A hug?

1546
01:40:35,020 --> 01:40:37,010
你知道最糟的是什么吗?
Do you know what the worst part of this is?

1547
01:40:37,190 --> 01:40:40,920
我不知道我是认为凶手就是艾伦
I can't tell if I wanted it to be Allen so bad

1548
01:40:41,090 --> 01:40:42,580
还是希望案子快点结束
because I actually thought it was him, or I just want all this to be over.

1549
01:40:42,760 --> 01:40:46,630
因为你认为是他  我也是啊
It's because you thought it was him. And I did, too.

1550
01:40:48,870 --> 01:40:50,560
这样吧  休息一阵子
You know what? Take some time off.

1551
01:40:50,740 --> 01:40:53,300
陪陪你老婆还有小孩
Spend some time with your wife and the kids.

1552
01:40:53,710 --> 01:40:57,070
带他们看球赛或是看电影
Go to Candlestick. See a movie.

1553
01:40:57,810 --> 01:40:59,300
(特别会议  旧金山警察局)

1554
01:40:59,480 --> 01:41:03,000
致旧金山市民  我很乐意每天杀一个人
To the city of San Francisco, I will enjoy killing one person every day

1555
01:41:03,180 --> 01:41:06,240
直到你们付我十万元
until you pay me $100,000.

1556
01:41:06,420 --> 01:41:09,750
同意的话  明天早上回复
If you agree, say so tomorrow morning

1557
01:41:09,920 --> 01:41:12,820
刊登在<旧金山纪事报>交友专栏
in the personal column San Francisco Chronicle,

1558
01:41:12,990 --> 01:41:14,820
我就会出面
and I will set up meeting.

1559
01:41:14,990 --> 01:41:16,820
如果得不到回复
If I do not hear from you,

1560
01:41:17,000 --> 01:41:20,160
我会先杀死一名天主教神父  或是
it will be my next pleasure to kill a Catholic priest or a...

1561
01:41:20,330 --> 01:41:21,460
(一个黑鬼)

1562
01:41:23,100 --> 01:41:25,040
天蝎座
Scorpio.

1563
01:41:27,010 --> 01:41:28,630
他一定是疯了
Who's out of their minds?

1564
01:41:28,810 --> 01:41:30,240
我得闪人
I've got to get out of here.

1565
01:41:30,410 --> 01:41:33,470
我要去哪里生出十万元?
Where the hell does he expect me to find $100,000?

1566
01:41:33,650 --> 01:41:36,310
市长  你不会真要付钱吧?
You're not thinking of paying him, are you, Mr. Mayor?

1567
01:41:36,480 --> 01:41:40,470
旧金山市政府不会付钱给凶手  好让他不去杀人
The city of San Francisco does not pay criminals not to commit a crime.

1568
01:41:42,850 --> 01:41:44,750
(<紧急追捕令>)

1569
01:42:03,740 --> 01:42:06,610
凶手最后胸口被开了一枪
The killer gets shot in the chest.

1570
01:42:06,780 --> 01:42:09,840
-结局就是这样  -我认识你吗?
-That's how it ends. -Do I know you?

1571
01:42:10,010 --> 01:42:13,510
我是罗伯・葛雷史密斯  保罗・艾瑞<纪事报>的同事
I'm Robert Graysmith. I work at the Chronicle with Paul Avery.

1572
01:42:13,690 --> 01:42:15,150
大卫・陶希  幸会
Dave Toschi. Nice to meet you.

1573
01:42:15,320 --> 01:42:17,810
那个卡拉汉对你的案子办得不错
Dave! That Harry Callahan did a hell of a job with your case.

1574
01:42:17,990 --> 01:42:21,290
是啊  他才不鸟正规的手续对吧?
Yeah. No need for due process, right?

1575
01:42:24,930 --> 01:42:26,990
-你在报社做什么?  -我画漫画
-What do you do at the Chronicle? -I'm a cartoonist.

1576
01:42:27,170 --> 01:42:29,500
-不错啊  -你会逮到他的
-That's nice. -You're gonna catch him.

1577
01:42:32,040 --> 01:42:34,660
老弟  这案子都拍成电影了
Pal, they're already making movies about it.

1578
01:42:42,750 --> 01:42:45,790
今天我们达成  一项协议
We today have concluded an agreement

1579
